Cloud and Mobile computing technologies have become an important part of scientific and infotechology developement in recent years and this seminar aims to introduce students to newest concepts and advances in these fields. Participants are expected to write an overview article on a chosen topic, give a oral presentation and taking active part of all the seminars.  
Topics covered by the seminar include: Cloud providers, cloud based software frameworks, cloud performance, large scale data processing in cloud, scientific computing in the cloud, developement of cloud based applications, migrating existing applications to the cloud, mobile applications, user interfaces, android development, iOS development, location based services, mobile application marketing, mobile web services.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The topics of this seminar are cloud computing software technologies, frameworks and services and the solutions, advances and new conceptions of mobile techonolgies. The goal of the students is to work independently with technocal and scientific materials, perform computational experiments and tests on connected technologies, write overview articles and practice oral presentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of this seminar, students will able to: 1.	Work through and understand the latest technical and scientific literature written in English. 2.	Summarise the content of technical and scientific literature in a scientific report style. 3.	Perform oral presentations on chosen subjects.
